#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8016
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom User Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8018
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By adding scripts to the auto-installation process you can customize the "
"installation according to your needs and take control in different stages of "
"the installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8024
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the auto-installation process, five types of scripts can be executed at "
"different points in time during the installation:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8029
#, no-c-format
msgid "All scripts need to be in the &lt;scripts&gt; section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8035
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>pre-scripts</literal> (very early, before anything else really "
"happens)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8041
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>postpartitioning-scripts</literal> (after partitioning and mounting "
"to <filename>/mnt</filename> but before RPM installation)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8047
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>chroot-scripts</literal> (after the package installation, before "
"the first boot)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8053
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>post-scripts</literal> (during the first boot of the installed "
"system, no services running)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8059
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>init-scripts</literal> (during the first boot of the installed "
"system, all services up and running)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8067
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pre-Install Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8068
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Executed before &yast; does any real change to the system (before "
"partitioning and package installation but after the hardware detection)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8073
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use a pre-script to modify your control file and let &ay; reread it. "
"Find your control file in <filename>/tmp/profile/autoinst.xml</filename>. "
"Adjust the file and store the modified version in <filename>/tmp/profile/"
"modified.xml</filename>. &ay; will read the modified file after the pre-"
"script finishes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8081
#, no-c-format
msgid "It is also possible to change the partitioning in your pre-script."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8085
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pre-Install Scripts with Confirmation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8086
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Pre-scripts are executed at an early stage of the installation. This means "
"if you have requested to confirm the installation, the pre-scripts will be "
"executed before the confirmation screen shows up (<literal>profile/install/"
"general/mode/confirm</literal>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8094
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pre-Install and Zypper"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8095
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To call <emphasis>zypper</emphasis> in the pre-install script you will need "
"to set the environment variable <emphasis>ZYPP_LOCKFILE_ROOT=\"/var/run/"
"autoyast\"</emphasis> to prevent conflicts with the running &yast; process."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pre-Install Script elements must be placed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;scripts&gt;\n"
"  &lt;pre-scripts config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;script&gt;\n"
"      ...\n"
"    &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/pre-scripts&gt;\n"
"&lt;/scripts&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8108
#, no-c-format
msgid "Post-partitioning Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Executed after &yast; has done the partitioning and written the fstab. The "
"empty system is already mounted to <filename>/mnt</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8114
#, no-c-format
msgid "Post-partitioning script elements must be placed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;scripts&gt;\n"
"  &lt;postpartitioning-scripts config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;script&gt;\n"
"      ...\n"
"    &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/postpartitioning-scripts&gt;\n"
"&lt;/scripts&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8121
#, no-c-format
msgid "Chroot Environment Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Chroot scripts are executed before the machine reboots for the first time. "
"You can execute chroot scripts before the installation chroots into the "
"installed system and configures the boot loader or you can execute a script "
"after the chroot into the installed system has happened (look at the "
"<literal>chrooted</literal> parameter for that)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Chroot Environment script elements must be placed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;scripts&gt;\n"
"  &lt;chroot-scripts config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;script&gt;\n"
"      ...\n"
"    &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/chroot-scripts&gt;\n"
"&lt;/scripts&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Post-Install Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These scripts are executed after &ay; has completed the system configuration "
"and after it has booted the system for the first time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to execute post scripts in an earlier phase while the "
"installation network is still up and before &ay; configures the system. To "
"run network-enabled post scripts, the boolean property "
"<literal>network_needed</literal> needs to be set to <literal>true</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8148
#, no-c-format
msgid "Post-install script elements must be placed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;scripts&gt;\n"
"    &lt;post-scripts config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;script&gt;\n"
"        ...\n"
"      &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/post-scripts&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/scripts&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Init Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8156
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These scripts are executed when &yast; has finished, during the initial boot "
"process after the network has been initialized. These final scripts are "
"executed using <filename>/usr/lib/YaST2/bin/autoyast-initscripts.sh</"
"filename> and are executed only once. Init scripts are configured using the "
"tag <emphasis>init-scripts</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following elements must be between the &lt;scripts&gt;&lt;init-scripts "
"config:type=\"list\"&gt;&lt;script&gt; ... &lt;/script&gt;&lt;/init-"
"scripts&gt;...&lt;/scripts&gt; tags"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8172
#, no-c-format
msgid "Init script XML representation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8197 ay_bigfile.xml:8327
#, no-c-format
msgid "location"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define a location from where the script gets fetched. Locations can be the "
"same as for the profile (HTTP, FTP, NFS, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;location\n"
"&gt;http://10.10.0.1/myInitScript.sh&lt;/location&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8208 ay_bigfile.xml:8229
#, no-c-format
msgid "Either &lt;location&gt; or &lt;source&gt; must be defined."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8217 ay_bigfile.xml:8347 ay_bigfile.xml:9213
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9312
#, no-c-format
msgid "source"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The script itself (source code), encapsulated in a CDATA tag. If you do not "
"want to put the whole shell script into the XML profile, use the location "
"parameter."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8226
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;source&gt;\n"
"&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"echo \"Testing the init script\" &gt;\n"
"/tmp/init_out.txt\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"&lt;/source&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8238
#, no-c-format
msgid "filename"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The file name of the script. It will be stored in a temporary directory "
"under <filename>/tmp</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8246
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;filename&gt;mynitScript5.sh&lt;/filename&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8249
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional in case you only have a single init script. The default name "
"(<filename>init-scripts</filename>) is used in this case. If having "
"specified more than one init script, you must set a unique name for each "
"script."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8260 ay_bigfile.xml:8508
#, no-c-format
msgid "rerun"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A script is only run once. Even if you use ayast_setup to run an XML file "
"multiple times, the script is only run once. Change this default behavior by "
"setting this boolean to <literal>true</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8270 ay_bigfile.xml:8518
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;rerun config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/rerun&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8273
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional. Default is <literal>false</literal> (scripts only run once)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8282
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When added to the control file manually, scripts need to be included in a "
"<emphasis>CDATA</emphasis> element to avoid confusion with the file syntax "
"and other tags defined in the control file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8290 ay_bigfile.xml:8299
#, no-c-format
msgid "Script XML Representation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All XML elements described below can be used for each of the script types "
"described above. The only exceptions are <literal>chrooted</literal> and "
"<literal>network_needed</literal>&mdash;they are only valid for chroot and "
"post-install scripts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define a location from where the script gets fetched. Locations can be the "
"same as for the control file (HTTP, FTP, NFS, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;location\n"
"&gt;http://10.10.0.1/myPreScript.sh&lt;/location&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8338 ay_bigfile.xml:8359
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Either <literal>location</literal> or <literal>source</literal> must be "
"defined."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8351
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The script itself (source code), encapsulated in a CDATA tag. If you do not "
"want to put the whole shell script into the XML control file, refer to the "
"location parameter."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8356
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;source&gt;\n"
"&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"echo \"Testing the pre script\" &gt; /tmp/pre-script_out.txt\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"&lt;/source&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8368 ay_bigfile.xml:9237
#, no-c-format
msgid "interpreter"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8372
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify the interpreter that must be used for the script. Supported options "
"are shell and perl."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8376 ay_bigfile.xml:9244
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;interpreter&gt;perl&lt;/interpreter&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8379
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional (default is <literal>shell</literal>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8387 ay_bigfile.xml:9294
#, no-c-format
msgid "file name"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8391
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The file name of the script. It will be stored in a temporary directory "
"under <filename>/tmp</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8395
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;filename&gt;myPreScript5.sh&lt;/filename&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. Default is the type of the script (pre-scripts in this case). If "
"you have more than one script, you should define different names for each "
"script."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8408 ay_bigfile.xml:9356
#, no-c-format
msgid "feedback"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8412
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this boolean is <literal>true</literal>, output and error messages of the "
"script (STDOUT and STDERR) will be shown in a pop-up. The user needs to "
"confirm them via the OK button."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8417 ay_bigfile.xml:9365
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;feedback config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/feedback&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8420 ay_bigfile.xml:9368
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional, default is <literal>false</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8428
#, no-c-format
msgid "feedback_type"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8432
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This can be <literal>message</literal>, <literal>warning</literal> or "
"<literal>error</literal>. Set the timeout for these pop-ups in the &lt;"
"report&gt; section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8437
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;feedback_type&gt;warning&lt;/feedback_type&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8440
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional, if missing, an always blocking pop-up is used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8448 ay_bigfile.xml:9376
#, no-c-format
msgid "debug"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8452
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this is <literal>true</literal>, every single line of a shell script is "
"logged. Perl scripts are run with warnings turned on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8456 ay_bigfile.xml:9383
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;debug config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/debug&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8459
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional, default is <literal>true</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8467
#, no-c-format
msgid "notification"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8471
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This text will be shown in a pop-up for the time the script is running in "
"the background."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8475
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;notification&gt;Please wait while script is running...&lt;/"
"notification&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8478
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional, if not configured, no notification pop-up will be shown."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8486
#, no-c-format
msgid "param-list"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8490
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to specify parameters given to the script being called. You "
"may have more than one <literal>param</literal> entry. They are concatenated "
"by a single space character on the script command line. If any shell quoting "
"should be necessary (for example to protect embedded spaces) you need to "
"include this."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8497
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;param-list&gt;\n"
"  &lt;param&gt;par1&lt;/param&gt;\n"
"  &lt;param&gt;par2 par3&lt;/param&gt;\n"
"  &lt;param&gt;\"par4.1 par4.2\"&lt;/param&gt;\n"
"&lt;/param-list&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8500
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional, if not configured, no parameters get passed to script."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8512
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A script is only run once. Even if you use <literal>ayast</literal>_setup to "
"run an XML file multiple times, the script is only run once. Change this "
"default behavior by setting this boolean to <literal>true</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8521
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional, default is <literal>false</literal> (scripts only run once)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8530
#, no-c-format
msgid "chrooted"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set to <literal>false</literal>, the installed system remains mounted at "
"<filename>/mnt</filename> and no chroot happens. The boot loader is not "
"installed either at this stage. Setting it to <literal>true</literal> means, "
"a chroot into <filename>/mnt</filename> is performed, where the installed "
"system is mounted. The boot loader is installed, and if you want to change "
"anything in the installed system, you do not need to use the <filename>/mnt</"
"filename> prefix anymore."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8544
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;chrooted config:type=\"boolean\"\n"
"&gt;true&lt;/chrooted&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8547
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional, default is <literal>false</literal>. This option is only available "
"for chroot environment scripts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8556
#, no-c-format
msgid "network_needed"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8561
#, no-c-format
msgid "FIXME: double check that. I'm very unsure if this is correct"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8562
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set to <literal>false</literal> the script will run after the &yast; "
"modules like the user configuration and everything else are done. The "
"network is configured but not up and running yet. With this value set to "
"<literal>true</literal>, the script runs before all &yast; modules are "
"configured. So there is no local user and no network is configured but the "
"installation network is still up and running (if you did a network "
"installation)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8571
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;network_needed config:type=\"boolean\"\n"
"&gt;true&lt;/network_needed&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8574
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional, default is <literal>false</literal>. This option is only available "
"for post-install scripts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8586
#, no-c-format
msgid "Script Example"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8588
#, no-c-format
msgid "Script Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8589
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\"?&gt;\n"
"&lt;!DOCTYPE profile&gt;\n"
"&lt;profile xmlns=\"http://www.suse.com/1.0/yast2ns\" xmlns:config=\"http://"
"www.suse.com/1.0/configns\"&gt;\n"
"&lt;scripts&gt;\n"
"  &lt;chroot-scripts config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;script&gt;\n"
"      &lt;chrooted config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/chrooted&gt;\n"
"      &lt;filename&gt;chroot.sh&lt;/filename&gt;\n"
"      &lt;interpreter&gt;shell&lt;/interpreter&gt;\n"
"      &lt;source&gt;&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"#!/bin/sh\n"
"echo \"Testing chroot (chrooted) scripts\"\n"
"ls\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/source&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"    &lt;script&gt;\n"
"      &lt;filename&gt;chroot.sh&lt;/filename&gt;\n"
"        &lt;interpreter&gt;shell&lt;/interpreter&gt;\n"
"        &lt;source&gt;&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"#!/bin/sh\n"
"echo \"Testing chroot scripts\"\n"
"df\n"
"cd /mnt\n"
"ls\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/source&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/chroot-scripts&gt;\n"
"    &lt;post-scripts config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;script&gt;\n"
"        &lt;filename&gt;post.sh&lt;/filename&gt;\n"
"        &lt;interpreter&gt;shell&lt;/interpreter&gt;\n"
"        &lt;source&gt;&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"#!/bin/sh\n"
"\n"
"echo \"Running Post-install script\"\n"
"systemctl start portmap\n"
"mount -a 192.168.1.1:/local /mnt\n"
"cp /mnt/test.sh /tmp\n"
"umount /mnt\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/source&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"      &lt;script&gt;\n"
"        &lt;filename&gt;post.pl&lt;/filename&gt;\n"
"        &lt;interpreter&gt;perl&lt;/interpreter&gt;\n"
"        &lt;source&gt;&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"#!/usr/bin/perl\n"
"print \"Running Post-install script\";\n"
"\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/source&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/post-scripts&gt;\n"
"    &lt;pre-scripts config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;script&gt;\n"
"        &lt;interpreter&gt;shell&lt;/interpreter&gt;\n"
"        &lt;location&gt;http://192.168.1.1/profiles/scripts/prescripts."
"sh&lt;/location&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"      &lt;script&gt;\n"
"        &lt;filename&gt;pre.sh&lt;/filename&gt;\n"
"        &lt;interpreter&gt;shell&lt;/interpreter&gt;\n"
"        &lt;source&gt;&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"#!/bin/sh\n"
"echo \"Running pre-install script\"\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/source&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/pre-scripts&gt;\n"
"    &lt;postpartitioning-scripts config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;script&gt;\n"
"        &lt;filename&gt;postpart.sh&lt;/filename&gt;\n"
"        &lt;interpreter&gt;shell&lt;/interpreter&gt;\n"
"        &lt;debug config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/debug&gt;\n"
"        &lt;feedback config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/feedback&gt;\n"
"        &lt;source&gt;&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"touch /mnt/testfile\n"
"echo Hi\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/source&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/postpartitioning-scripts&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/scripts&gt;\n"
"&lt;/profile&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8591
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After installation is finished, the scripts and the output logs can be found "
"in the directory <filename>/var/adm/autoinstall</filename>. The scripts are "
"located in the subdirectory <filename>scripts</filename> and the output logs "
"in the <filename>log</filename> directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8597
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The log consists of the output produced when executing the shell scripts "
"using the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"/bin/sh -x <replaceable>SCRIPT_NAME</replaceable> 2&amp;&gt;/var/adm/"
"autoinstall/logs/<replaceable>SCRIPT_NAME</replaceable>.log"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8605
#, no-c-format
msgid "System Variables (Sysconfig)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8607
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the sysconfig resource, it is possible to define configuration "
"variables in the sysconfig repository (<filename>/etc/sysconfig</filename>) "
"directly. Sysconfig variables, offer the possibility to fine-tune many "
"system components and environment variables exactly to your needs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8615
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following example shows how a variable can be set using the sysconfig "
"resource."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8621
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sysconfig Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;sysconfig config:type=\"list\" &gt;\n"
"  &lt;sysconfig_entry&gt;\n"
"    &lt;sysconfig_key&gt;XNTPD_INITIAL_NTPDATE&lt;/sysconfig_key&gt;\n"
"    &lt;sysconfig_path&gt;/etc/sysconfig/xntp&lt;/sysconfig_path&gt;\n"
"    &lt;sysconfig_value&gt;ntp.host.com&lt;/sysconfig_value&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/sysconfig_entry&gt;\n"
"  &lt;sysconfig_entry&gt;\n"
"    &lt;sysconfig_key&gt;HTTP_PROXY&lt;/sysconfig_key&gt;\n"
"    &lt;sysconfig_path&gt;/etc/sysconfig/proxy&lt;/sysconfig_path&gt;\n"
"    &lt;sysconfig_value&gt;proxy.host.com:3128&lt;/sysconfig_value&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/sysconfig_entry&gt;\n"
"  &lt;sysconfig_entry&gt;\n"
"    &lt;sysconfig_key&gt;FTP_PROXY&lt;/sysconfig_key&gt;\n"
"    &lt;sysconfig_path&gt;/etc/sysconfig/proxy&lt;/sysconfig_path&gt;\n"
"    &lt;sysconfig_value&gt;proxy.host.com:3128&lt;/sysconfig_value&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/sysconfig_entry&gt;\n"
"&lt;/sysconfig&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8623
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Both relative and absolute paths can be provided. If no absolute path is "
"given, it is treated as a sysconfig file under the <filename>/etc/sysconfig</"
"filename> directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8631
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding Complete Configurations"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For many applications and services you may have a configuration file which "
"should be copied to the appropriate location on the installed system. For "
"example, if you are installing a Web server, you may have a server "
"configuration file (<filename>httpd.conf</filename>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8640
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using this resource, you can embed the file into the control file by "
"specifying the final path on the installed system. &yast; will copy this "
"file to the specified location."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8646
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This feature requires the <package>autoyast2</package> package to be "
"installed. If the package is missing, &ay; will automatically install the "
"package if it is missing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8652
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can specify the <literal>file_location</literal> where the file should "
"be retrieved from. This can also be a location on the network such as an "
"HTTP server: <literal>&lt;file_location&gt;http://my.server.site/issue&lt;/"
"file_location&gt;</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can create directories by specifying a <literal>file_path</literal> that "
"ends with a slash."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8665 ay_bigfile.xml:8678
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dumping files into the installed system"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8666
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;files config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;file&gt;\n"
"    &lt;file_path&gt;/etc/apache2/httpd.conf&lt;/file_path&gt;\n"
"    &lt;file_contents&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"some content\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"\n"
"    &lt;/file_contents&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/file&gt;\n"
"  &lt;file&gt;\n"
"    &lt;file_path&gt;/mydir/a/b/c/&lt;/file_path&gt; &lt;!-- create "
"directory --&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/file&gt;\n"
"&lt;/files&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8669
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A more advanced example is shown below. This configuration will create a "
"file using the content supplied in <literal>file_contents</literal> and "
"change the permissions and ownership of the file. After the file has been "
"copied to the system, a script is executed. This can be used to modify the "
"file and prepare it for the client's environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8679
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;files config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;file&gt;\n"
"    &lt;file_path&gt;/etc/someconf.conf&lt;/file_path&gt;\n"
"    &lt;file_contents&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"some content\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"\n"
"    &lt;/file_contents&gt;\n"
"    &lt;file_owner&gt;&exampleuser_plain;.users&lt;/file_owner&gt;\n"
"    &lt;file_permissions&gt;444&lt;/file_permissions&gt;\n"
"    &lt;file_script&gt;\n"
"      &lt;interpreter&gt;shell&lt;/interpreter&gt;\n"
"      &lt;source&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"#!/bin/sh\n"
"\n"
"echo \"Testing file scripts\" &gt;&gt; /etc/someconf.conf\n"
"df\n"
"cd /mnt\n"
"ls\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"\n"
"      &lt;/source&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/file_script&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/file&gt;\n"
"&lt;/files&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8683
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ask the User for Values during Installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You have the option to let the user decide the values of specific parts of "
"the control file during the installation. If you use this feature, a pop-up "
"will ask the user to enter a specific part of the control file during "
"installation. If you want a full auto installation, but the user should set "
"the password of the local account, you can do this via the <literal>ask</"
"literal> directive in the control file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8699
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;general&gt;\n"
"  &lt;ask-list config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;ask&gt;\n"
"      ...\n"
"    &lt;/ask&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/ask-list&gt;\n"
"&lt;/general&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8702
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ask the User for Values: XML representation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8727 ay_bigfile.xml:11986
#, no-c-format
msgid "question"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8731
#, no-c-format
msgid "The question you want to ask the user."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8734
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;question&gt;Enter the LDAP server&lt;/question&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8737
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default value is the path to the element (the path often looks strange, "
"so we recommend entering a question)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8741
#, no-c-format
msgid "emap 2011-11-04: not sure I understand this."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8747
#, no-c-format
msgid "default"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8751
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set a preselection for the user. A text entry will be filled out with this "
"value. A check box will be true or false and a selection will have the given "
"value preselected."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8756
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;default&gt;dc=suse,dc=de&lt;/default&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8767
#, no-c-format
msgid "help"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8771
#, no-c-format
msgid "An optional help text that is shown on the left side of the question."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8775
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;help&gt;Enter the LDAP server address.&lt;/help&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8786 ay_bigfile.xml:11968
#, no-c-format
msgid "title"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8790
#, no-c-format
msgid "An optional title that is shown above the questions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8793
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;title&gt;LDAP server&lt;/title&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8808
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The type of the element you want to change. Possible values are "
"<literal>symbol</literal>, <literal>boolean</literal>, <literal>string</"
"literal> and <literal>integer</literal>. The file system in the partition "
"section is a symbol, while the <literal>encrypted</literal> element in the "
"user configuration is a boolean. You can see the type of that element if you "
"look in your control file at the <literal>config:type=\"....\"</literal> "
"attribute. You can also use <literal>static_text</literal> as type. A "
"<literal>static_text</literal> is a text that does not require any user "
"input and can be used to show information not included in the help text."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8821
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;type&gt;symbol&lt;/type&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8824
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. The default is <literal>string</literal>. If type is "
"<literal>symbol</literal>, you must provide the selection element too (see "
"below)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8834
#, no-c-format
msgid "password"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8838
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this boolean is set to <literal>true</literal>, a password dialog pops up "
"instead of a simple text entry. Setting this to <literal>true</literal> only "
"makes sense if <literal>type</literal> is string."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8844
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;password config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/password&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8855
#, no-c-format
msgid "pathlist"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8859
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A list of <literal>path</literal> elements. A path is a comma separated list "
"of elements that describes the path to the element you want to change. For "
"example, the LDAP server element can be found in the control file in the "
"<literal>&lt;ldap&gt;&lt;ldap_server&gt;</literal> section. So if you want "
"to change that value, you need to set the path to <literal>ldap,ldap_server</"
"literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8868
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;pathlist config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;path&gt;networking,dns,hostname&lt;/path&gt;\n"
"  &lt;path&gt;...&lt;/path&gt;\n"
"&lt;/pathlist&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8869
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To change the password of the first user in the control file, you need to "
"set the path to <literal>users,0,user_password</literal>. The <literal>0</"
"literal> indicates the first user in the &lt;users config:type=\"list\"&gt; "
"list of users in the control file. <literal>1</literal> would be the second "
"one, and so on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8876
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;users config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;user&gt;\n"
"    &lt;username&gt;root&lt;/username&gt;\n"
"    &lt;user_password&gt;password to change&lt;/user_password&gt;\n"
"    &lt;encrypted config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/encrypted&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/user&gt;\n"
"  &lt;user&gt;\n"
"    &lt;username&gt;&exampleuser_plain;&lt;/username&gt;\n"
"    &lt;user_password&gt;password to change&lt;/user_password&gt;\n"
"    &lt;encrypted config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/encrypted&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/user&gt;\n"
"&lt;/users&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8880
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This information is optional but you should at least provide <literal>path</"
"literal> or <literal>file</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8889
#, no-c-format
msgid "file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8893
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can store the answer to a question in a file, to use it in one of your "
"scripts later. If you ask during <literal>stage=initial</literal> and you "
"want to use the answer in stage&nbsp;2, then you need to copy the answer-"
"file in a chroot script that is running as <literal>chrooted=false</"
"literal>. Use the command: <command>cp /tmp/my_answer /mnt/tmp/</command>. "
"The reason is that <filename>/tmp</filename> in stage&nbsp;1 is in the RAM "
"disk and will be lost after the reboot, but the installed system is already "
"mounted at <filename>/mnt/</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8904
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;file&gt;/tmp/answer_hostname&lt;/file&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8907
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This information is optional, but you should at least provide <literal>path</"
"literal> or <literal>file</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8915
#, no-c-format
msgid "stage"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8920
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Stage configures the installation stage in which the question pops up. You "
"can set this value to <literal>cont</literal> or <literal>initial</literal>. "
"<literal>initial</literal> means the pop-up comes up very early in the "
"installation, shortly after the pre-script has run. <literal>cont</literal> "
"means, that the dialog with the question comes after the first reboot when "
"the system boots for the very first time. Questions you answer during the "
"<literal>initial</literal> stage will write their answer into the control "
"file on the hard disk. You should know that if you enter clear text "
"passwords during <literal>initial</literal>. Of course it does not make "
"sense to ask for the file system to use during the <literal>cont</literal> "
"phase. The hard disk is already partitioned at that stage and the question "
"will have no effect."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8935
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;stage&gt;cont&lt;/stage&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8938
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional. The default is <literal>initial</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8946
#, no-c-format
msgid "selection"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8950
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The selection element contains a list of <literal>entry</literal> elements. "
"Each entry represents a possible option for the user to choose. The user "
"cannot enter a value in a text box, but he can choose from a list of values."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8956
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;selection config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;entry&gt;\n"
"    &lt;value&gt;\n"
"        btrfs\n"
"    &lt;/value&gt;\n"
"    &lt;label&gt;\n"
"        Btrfs File System\n"
"    &lt;/label&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/entry&gt;\n"
"  &lt;entry&gt;\n"
"    &lt;value&gt;\n"
"        ext3\n"
"    &lt;/value&gt;\n"
"    &lt;label&gt;\n"
"        Extended3 File System\n"
"    &lt;/label&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/entry&gt;\n"
"&lt;/selection&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8959
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional for <literal>type=string</literal>, not possible for "
"<literal>type=boolean</literal> and mandatory for <literal>type=symbol</"
"literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8969
#, no-c-format
msgid "dialog"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8973
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can ask more than one question per dialog. To do so, specify the dialog-"
"id with an integer. All questions with the same dialog-id belong to the same "
"dialog. The dialogs are sorted by the id too."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8979
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;dialog config:type=\"integer\"&gt;3&lt;/dialog&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8990 ay_bigfile.xml:11945
#, no-c-format
msgid "element"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8994
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"you can have more than one question per dialog. To make that possible you "
"need to specify the element-id with an integer. The questions in a dialog "
"are sorted by id."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:8999
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;element config:type=\"integer\"&gt;1&lt;/element&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9002
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional (see dialog)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9010
#, no-c-format
msgid "width"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9014
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can increase the default width of dialog. If there are multiple width "
"specifications per dialog, the largest one is used. The number is roughly "
"equivalent to the number of characters."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9019
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;width config:type=\"integer\"&gt;50&lt;/width&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9030
#, no-c-format
msgid "height"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9034
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can increase default height of dialog. If there are multiple height "
"specifications per dialog, largest one is used. The number is roughly "
"equivalent to number of lines."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9039
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;height config:type=\"integer\"&gt;15&lt;/height&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9050
#, no-c-format
msgid "frametitle"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9054
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can have more than one question per dialog. Each question on a dialog "
"has a frame that can have a frame title, a small caption for each question. "
"You can put multiple elements into one frame. They need to have the same "
"frame title."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9060
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;frametitle&gt;User data&lt;/frametitle&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9063
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional. Default is no frame title."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9071
#, no-c-format
msgid "script"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9075
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can run scripts after a question has been answered (see the table below "
"for detailed instructions about scripts)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9079
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;script&gt;...&lt;/script&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9082
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional (default is no script)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9090
#, no-c-format
msgid "ok_label"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9094
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can change the label on the <guimenu>Ok</guimenu> button. The last "
"element that specifies the label for a dialog wins."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9098
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;ok_label&gt;Finish&lt;/ok_label&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9109
#, no-c-format
msgid "back_label"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can change the label on the <guimenu>Back</guimenu> button. The last "
"element that specifies the label for a dialog wins."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9117
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;back_label&gt;change values&lt;/back_label&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can specify an integer here that is used as timeout in seconds. If the "
"user does not answer the question before the timeout, the default value is "
"taken as answer. When the user touches or changes any widget in the dialog, "
"the timeout is turned off and the dialog needs to be confirmed via "
"<guimenu>Ok</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9139 ay_bigfile.xml:12014
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;timeout config:type=\"integer\"&gt;30&lt;/timeout&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. A missing value is interpreted as <literal>0</literal>, which "
"means that there is no timeout."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9151
#, no-c-format
msgid "default_value_script"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can run scripts to set the default value for a question (see <xref "
"linkend=\"CreateProfile.Ask.default_value\"/> for detailed instructions "
"about default value scripts). This feature is useful if you can "
"<literal>calculate</literal> a default value, especially in combination with "
"the <literal>timeout</literal> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9162
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;default_value_script&gt;...&lt;/default_value_script&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9165
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional. Default is no script."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9175
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default Value Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can run scripts to set the default value for a question. This feature is "
"useful if you can <literal>calculate</literal> a default value, especially "
"in combination with the <literal>timeout</literal> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;general&gt;\n"
"  &lt;ask-list config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;ask&gt;\n"
"      &lt;default_value_script&gt;\n"
"        ...\n"
"      &lt;/default_value_script&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/ask&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/ask-list&gt;\n"
"&lt;/general&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default Value Scripts: XML representation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The source code of the script. Whatever you <command>echo</command> to "
"STDOUT will be used as default value for the ask-dialog. If your script has "
"an exit code other than 0, the normal default element is used. Take care you "
"use <command>echo -n</command> to suppress the <literal>\\n</literal> and "
"that you echo reasonable values and not <quote>okay</quote> for a boolean"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9226 ay_bigfile.xml:9325
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;source&gt;...&lt;/source&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9229 ay_bigfile.xml:9328
#, no-c-format
msgid "This value is required, otherwise nothing would be executed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9241
#, no-c-format
msgid "The interpreter to use."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9247
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default value is <literal>shell</literal>. You can also set <filename>/"
"bin/myinterpreter</filename> as value."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9259
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9260
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can run scripts after a question has been answered."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;general&gt;\n"
"  &lt;ask-list config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;ask&gt;\n"
"      &lt;script&gt;\n"
"        ...\n"
"      &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/ask&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/ask-list&gt;\n"
"&lt;/general&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9269
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scripts: XML representation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9298
#, no-c-format
msgid "The file name of the script."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9301
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;filename&gt;my_ask_script.sh&lt;/filename&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9304
#, no-c-format
msgid "The default is ask_script.sh"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9316
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The source code of the script. Together with <literal>rerun_on_error</"
"literal> activated, you check the value that was entered for sanity. Your "
"script can create a file <filename>/tmp/next_dialog</filename> with a dialog "
"id specifying the next dialog &ay; will raise. A value of -1 terminates the "
"ask sequence. If that file is not created, &ay; will run the dialogs in the "
"normal order (since 11.0 only)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9336
#, no-c-format
msgid "environment"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A boolean that passes the value of the answer to the question as an "
"environment variable to the script. The variable is named <envar>VAL</envar>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9345
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;environment config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/environment&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9348
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional. Default is <literal>false</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A boolean that turns on feedback for the script execution. STDOUT will be "
"displayed in a pop-up window that must be confirmed after the script "
"execution."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9380
#, no-c-format
msgid "A boolean that turns on debugging for the script execution."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional, default is <literal>true</literal>. This value needs "
"<literal>feedback</literal> to be turned on, too."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9395
#, no-c-format
msgid "rerun_on_error"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9399
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A boolean that keeps the dialog open until the script has an exit code of 0 "
"(zero). So you can parse and check the answers the user gave in the script "
"and display an error with the <literal>feedback</literal> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9405
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;rerun_on_error config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/rerun_on_error&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9408
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional, default is <literal>false</literal>. This value should be used "
"together with the feedback option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9417
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Below you can see an example of the usage of the <literal>ask</literal> "
"feature."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;general&gt;\n"
"  &lt;ask-list config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;ask&gt;\n"
"      &lt;pathlist config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"        &lt;path&gt;ldap,ldap_server&lt;/path&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/pathlist&gt;\n"
"      &lt;stage&gt;cont&lt;/stage&gt;\n"
"      &lt;help&gt;Choose your server depending on your department&lt;/"
"help&gt;\n"
"      &lt;selection config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"        &lt;entry&gt;\n"
"          &lt;value&gt;ldap1.mydom.de&lt;/value&gt;\n"
"          &lt;label&gt;LDAP for development&lt;/label&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/entry&gt;\n"
"        &lt;entry&gt;\n"
"          &lt;value&gt;ldap2.mydom.de&lt;/value&gt;\n"
"          &lt;label&gt;LDAP for sales&lt;/label&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/entry&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/selection&gt;\n"
"      &lt;default&gt;ldap2.mydom.de&lt;/default&gt;\n"
"      &lt;default_value_script&gt;\n"
"        &lt;source&gt; &lt;![CDATA[\n"
"echo -n \"ldap1.mydom.de\"\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/source&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/default_value_script&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/ask&gt;\n"
"    &lt;ask&gt;\n"
"      &lt;pathlist config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"        &lt;path&gt;networking,dns,hostname&lt;/path&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/pathlist&gt;\n"
"      &lt;question&gt;Enter Hostname&lt;/question&gt;\n"
"      &lt;stage&gt;initial&lt;/stage&gt;\n"
"      &lt;default&gt;enter your hostname here&lt;/default&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/ask&gt;\n"
"    &lt;ask&gt;\n"
"      &lt;pathlist config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"        &lt;path&gt;partitioning,0,partitions,0,filesystem&lt;/path&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/pathlist&gt;\n"
"      &lt;question&gt;File System&lt;/question&gt;\n"
"      &lt;type&gt;symbol&lt;/type&gt;\n"
"      &lt;selection config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"        &lt;entry&gt;\n"
"          &lt;value config:type=\"symbol\"&gt;ext4&lt;/value&gt;\n"
"          &lt;label&gt;default File System (recommended)&lt;/label&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/entry&gt;\n"
"        &lt;entry&gt;\n"
"          &lt;value config:type=\"symbol\"&gt;ext3&lt;/value&gt;\n"
"          &lt;label&gt;Fallback File System&lt;/label&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/entry&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/selection&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/ask&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/ask-list&gt;\n"
"&lt;/general&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following example shows a to choose between &ay; control files. &ay; "
"will read the <filename>modified.xml</filename> file again after the ask-"
"dialogs are done. This way you can fetch a complete new control file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9428
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;general&gt;\n"
"  &lt;ask-list config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;ask&gt;\n"
"      &lt;selection config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"        &lt;entry&gt;\n"
"          &lt;value&gt;part1.xml&lt;/value&gt;\n"
"          &lt;label&gt;Simple partitioning&lt;/label&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/entry&gt;\n"
"        &lt;entry&gt;\n"
"          &lt;value&gt;part2.xml&lt;/value&gt;\n"
"          &lt;label&gt;encrypted /tmp&lt;/label&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/entry&gt;\n"
"        &lt;entry&gt;\n"
"          &lt;value&gt;part3.xml&lt;/value&gt;\n"
"          &lt;label&gt;LVM&lt;/label&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/entry&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/selection&gt;\n"
"      &lt;title&gt;XML Profile&lt;/title&gt;\n"
"      &lt;question&gt;Choose a profile&lt;/question&gt;\n"
